name: Procedure Legal Basis (ID)
nameLabel: Legal basis of the procedure (ELI - CELEX)
descriptionLabel: The legal basis (e.g. a Union or national legal act) under which the procurement procedure takes place or, in case of prior information notices, under which the procurement procedure(s) will take place.

name: Procedure Legal Basis (Description)
descriptionLabel: The legal basis (e.g. a Union or national legal act) under which the procurement procedure takes place or, in case of prior information notices, under which the procurement procedure(s) will take place.

name: Procedure Legal Basis (NoID)
descriptionLabel: The legal basis (e.g. a Union or national legal act) under which the procurement procedure takes place or, in case of prior information notices, under which the procurement procedure(s) will take place.

name: Procedure Legal Basis (NoID Description)
descriptionLabel: The legal basis (e.g. a Union or national legal act) under which the procurement procedure takes place or, in case of prior information notices, under which the procurement procedure(s) will take place.

name: Procedure Legal Basis
descriptionLabel: The legal basis (e.g. a Union or national legal act) under which the procurement procedure takes place or, in case of prior information notices, under which the procurement procedure(s) will take place.

name: Notice Type
descriptionLabel: The type of notice according to procurement legislation.

name: Form Type
descriptionLabel: The type of form according to procurement legislation.

name: Procedure Identifier
descriptionLabel: The European Public Procurement Procedure Identifier, a unique identifier of a procurement procedure. Including this identifier in all published versions of this notice (e.g. published on TED, national publication portals, regional publication portals) allows unique identification of procurement procedures around the Union.

name: Notice Dispatch Date
descriptionLabel: The date and time when the notice has been sent for publication by the buyer.

name: Notice Dispatch Time
descriptionLabel: The date and time when the notice has been sent for publication by the buyer.

name: Strategic Procurement
descriptionLabel: The procurement procedure aims at reducing the environmental impacts of the procurement, fulfilling social objectives and/or buying an innovative work, supply or service.

name: Cross Border Law
descriptionLabel: The applicable law when buyers from different countries procure together within one procurement procedure.

name: Cross Border Law Description
descriptionLabel: The applicable law when buyers from different countries procure together within one procurement procedure.

name: Activity Authority
descriptionLabel: The main activity of the contracting authority.

name: Buyer Legal Type
descriptionLabel: The type of buyer according to procurement legislation (e.g. central government authority, body governed by public law, public undertaking).

name: Additional Information Deadline
descriptionLabel: The time limit for requesting additional information about the procurement procedure.

name: Additional Information Deadline
descriptionLabel: The time limit for requesting additional information about the procurement procedure.

name: Additional Information Deadline
descriptionLabel: The time limit for requesting additional information about the procurement procedure.

name: Additional Information Deadline
descriptionLabel: The time limit for requesting additional information about the procurement procedure.

name: Documents Restricted
nameLabel: Access to certain procurement documents is restricted
descriptionLabel: The access to certain procurement documents is restricted.

name: Documents Restricted
nameLabel: Access to certain procurement documents is restricted
descriptionLabel: The access to certain procurement documents is restricted.

name: Documents URL
descriptionLabel: The internet address for accessing (the non-restricted part of) the procurement documents. For all notices except prior information notices, the address shall give access that is direct (i.e. the exact webpage with the documents, not a general website), unrestricted (e.g. no registration), full (i.e. the procurement documents are complete) and free of charge and the documents shall be available already at the time of the publication of the notice.

name: Documents URL
descriptionLabel: The internet address for accessing (the non-restricted part of) the procurement documents. For all notices except prior information notices, the address shall give access that is direct (i.e. the exact webpage with the documents, not a general website), unrestricted (e.g. no registration), full (i.e. the procurement documents are complete) and free of charge and the documents shall be available already at the time of the publication of the notice.

name: Organisation Part Name
descriptionLabel: The name of a part of an organisation (e.g. the relevant department of a large buyer).

name: Part Name
descriptionLabel: The name of a part of an organisation (e.g. the relevant department of a large buyer).

name: SubmissionElectronic
descriptionLabel: Whether economic operators are required, allowed, or not allowed to submit tenders, requests to participate, or expressions of interest electronically.

name: Submission URL
descriptionLabel: The internet address for submission of tenders, requests to participate, or expressions of interest by electronic means. The address shall be as direct as possible (ideally a dedicated address for the electronic submission, not just a general website).

name: Submission Nonelectronic Justification
nameLabel: Justification for why electronic submission is not possible
descriptionLabel: The justification for electronic submission of tenders, requests to participate, or expressions of interest not being possible.

name: Title
descriptionLabel: The name of the procurement procedure or lot.

name: Title
descriptionLabel: The name of the procurement procedure or lot.

name: Title
descriptionLabel: The name of the procurement procedure or lot.

name: Title
descriptionLabel: The name of the procurement procedure or lot.

name: Internal Identifier
descriptionLabel: The internal identifier used for files regarding the procurement procedure or lot before a procedure identifier is given (e.g. coming from the buyer's document management system or procurement planning system).

name: Internal Identifier
descriptionLabel: The internal identifier used for files regarding the procurement procedure or lot before a procedure identifier is given (e.g. coming from the buyer's document management system or procurement planning system).

name: Internal Identifier
descriptionLabel: The internal identifier used for files regarding the procurement procedure or lot before a procedure identifier is given (e.g. coming from the buyer's document management system or procurement planning system).

name: Internal Identifier
descriptionLabel: The internal identifier used for files regarding the procurement procedure or lot before a procedure identifier is given (e.g. coming from the buyer's document management system or procurement planning system).

name: Main Nature
descriptionLabel: The main nature (e.g. works) of what is being bought. In case of mixed procurement (e.g. a procedure for both works and services), the main nature may be, for example, the one with the highest estimated value. This information shall be given for the whole procedure.

name: Main Nature
descriptionLabel: The main nature (e.g. works) of what is being bought. In case of mixed procurement (e.g. a procedure for both works and services), the main nature may be, for example, the one with the highest estimated value. This information shall be given for the whole procedure.

name: Main Nature
descriptionLabel: The main nature (e.g. works) of what is being bought. In case of mixed procurement (e.g. a procedure for both works and services), the main nature may be, for example, the one with the highest estimated value. This information shall be given for the whole procedure.

name: Description
descriptionLabel: The description of the nature and quantity of what is being bought or of the needs and requirements that shall be met in this procedure or lot. In case of a modification notice, the description of the procurement before and after the modification.

name: Description
descriptionLabel: The description of the nature and quantity of what is being bought or of the needs and requirements that shall be met in this procedure or lot. In case of a modification notice, the description of the procurement before and after the modification.

name: Description
descriptionLabel: The description of the nature and quantity of what is being bought or of the needs and requirements that shall be met in this procedure or lot. In case of a modification notice, the description of the procurement before and after the modification.

name: Description
descriptionLabel: The description of the nature and quantity of what is being bought or of the needs and requirements that shall be met in this procedure or lot. In case of a modification notice, the description of the procurement before and after the modification.

name: Quantity
descriptionLabel: The number of units required.

name: Classification Type (e.g. CPV)
descriptionLabel: The type of classification describing the purchase (e.g. the CPV).

descriptionLabel: The type of classification describing the purchase (e.g. the CPV).

descriptionLabel: The type of classification describing the purchase (e.g. the CPV).

name: Estimated Value
descriptionLabel: The estimated value of the procurement procedure or lot, over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Estimated Value
descriptionLabel: The estimated value of the procurement procedure or lot, over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Estimated Value
descriptionLabel: The estimated value of the procurement procedure or lot, over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Estimated Value
descriptionLabel: The estimated value of the procurement procedure or lot, over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Lots Max Allowed
nameLabel: Maximum number of lots for which one tenderer can submit tenders
descriptionLabel: The maximum number of lots for which one tenderer can submit tenders.

name: Lots Max Awarded
nameLabel: Maximum number of lots for which contracts can be awarded to one tenderer
descriptionLabel: The maximum number of lots for which contract(s) can be awarded to one tenderer.

name: Duration Period
descriptionLabel: The (estimated) period from the start to the end of the contract, framework agreement, dynamic purchasing system or qualification system. This shall include any options and renewals.

name: Duration Period
descriptionLabel: The (estimated) period from the start to the end of the contract, framework agreement, dynamic purchasing system or qualification system. This shall include any options and renewals.

name: Selection Criteria Second Stage Invite
nameLabel: The criteria will be used to select the candidates to be invited for the second stage of the procedure
descriptionLabel: The criteria (or criterion) will (only) be used to select the candidates to be invited for the second stage of the procedure (if a maximum number of candidates was set).

name: Following Contract
nameLabel: Any service contract following the contest will be awarded to one of the winners of the contest
descriptionLabel: Any service contract following the contest will be awarded to one of the winners of the contest.

name: Jury Decision Binding
nameLabel: The decision of the jury is binding on the buyer
descriptionLabel: The decision of the jury is binding on the buyer.

name: Prize Rank
descriptionLabel: The place (e.g. first place, second place) in a design contest, innovation partnership or competitive dialogue that receives the prize.

name: Rewards Other
descriptionLabel: Further information about follow-up contracts, prizes and payments (for example non-monetary prizes, payments given for participation).

name: Jury Member Name
descriptionLabel: A name of the jury member.

name: Participant Name
descriptionLabel: A name of an already selected participant. A participant could have been selected already at the time of the publication of the design contest notice because, for example, the information about the participation of a world-renowned architect is intended to promote the contest amongst other potential participants.

name: Minimum Candidates
nameLabel: Minimum number of candidates to be invited for the second stage of the procedure
descriptionLabel: The minimum number of candidates to be invited for the second stage of the procedure.

name: Maximum Candidates Number
nameLabel: Maximum number of candidates to be invited for the second stage of the procedure
descriptionLabel: The maximum number of candidates to be invited for the second stage of the procedure.

name: Successive Reduction Indicator (Lot)
nameLabel: The procedure will take place in successive stages. At each stage, some participants may be eliminated
descriptionLabel: The procedure will take place in successive stages. In each stage, some participants may be eliminated.

name: Options Description
nameLabel: The buyer reserves the right for additional purchases from the contractor, as described here
descriptionLabel: The description of the options.

name: Renewal Description
descriptionLabel: Any other information about the renewal(s).

name: Renewal Maximum
descriptionLabel: The maximum number of times the contract can be renewed. By renewing, the buyer reserves the right (i.e. not an obligation) to renew the contract (i.e. extend its duration) without a new procurement procedure. For example, a contract may be valid for one year and the buyer may keep a possibility to renew it (e.g. once, twice) for another three months, if he is content with the services he received.

name: EU Funds
nameLabel: The procurement is at least partially financed by European Union funds
descriptionLabel: The procurement is at least partially financed by Union funds such as the European Structural and Investment Funds or grants awarded by the Union.

name: Variants
descriptionLabel: Whether tenderers are required, allowed, or not allowed to submit tenders which fulfil the buyer's needs differently than as proposed in the procurement documents. Further conditions for submitting variant tenders are in the procurement documents.

name: Subcontracting Obligation Minimum
nameLabel: Minimum percentage of the contract value that the contractor must subcontract
descriptionLabel: The minimum percentage of the contract value that the contractor must subcontract using the competitive procedure described in Title III of European Parliament and Council Directive 2009/81/EC.

name: Subcontracting Obligation
nameLabel: An obligation to be met by the tenderer concerning subcontracting
descriptionLabel: An obligation to be met by the tenderer concerning subcontracting.

name: Exclusion Grounds
descriptionLabel: The brief description of criteria regarding the personal situation of tenderers that may lead to their exclusion. This shall include a list of all such criteria and indicate required information (e.g. self-declaration, documentation). This may also include specific national exclusion grounds.

name: Exclusion Grounds
descriptionLabel: The brief description of criteria regarding the personal situation of tenderers that may lead to their exclusion. This shall include a list of all such criteria and indicate required information (e.g. self-declaration, documentation). This may also include specific national exclusion grounds.

name: Terms Performance
nameLabel: Conditions relating to the performance of the contract
descriptionLabel: The main information about the performance of the contract (e.g. intermediary deliverables, compensation for damages, intellectual property rights).

name: Reserved Participation
descriptionLabel: Whether participation is reserved for specific organisations (e.g. sheltered workshops, organisations pursuing a public service mission).

name: Reserved Participation
descriptionLabel: Whether participation is reserved for specific organisations (e.g. sheltered workshops, organisations pursuing a public service mission).

name: Guarantee Required Description
descriptionLabel: The description of the financial guarantee required from the tenderer when submitting a tender. The guarantee can take the form of, for example, a payment to the buyer or a document from a bank. Typically, the guarantee would be forfeit when a tenderer has won the contract but then refused to sign it.

name: Tenderer Legal Form Description
nameLabel: Legal form that must be taken by a group of tenderers that is awarded a contract
descriptionLabel: The legal form that must be taken by a group of tenderers that is awarded a contract.

name: Terms Financial
descriptionLabel: The main information about financing and payment and/or reference to any provisions that govern them.

name: Security Clearance Deadline
descriptionLabel: The time limit by which tenderers who do not hold a security clearance may obtain it.

name: Performing Staff Qualification
nameLabel: The names and professional qualifications of the staff assigned to perform the contract must be given
descriptionLabel: Whether the names and professional qualifications of the staff assigned to perform the contract must be given.

name: Procedure Features
descriptionLabel: The main features of the procedure (e.g. description of the individual stage(s)) and information about where the full rules for the procedure can be found. This information shall be given when the procedure is not one of those mentioned in the procurement Directives. This can be the case for example for concessions, for social and other specific services, and in case of voluntary publication of procurement procedures below the EU procurement thresholds.

name: Electronic Ordering
descriptionLabel: Electronic ordering will be used.

name: Electronic Payment
descriptionLabel: Electronic payment will be used.

name: Recurrence
descriptionLabel: Procurement whose purpose is likely to also be included in another procedure in the foreseeable future. (For example, a regularly re-tendered municipal service. This does not include awarding multiple contracts within a single qualification system, framework agreement, or a dynamic purchasing system.)

name: Recurrence Description
descriptionLabel: Any additional information about recurrence (e.g. estimated timing).

name: Submission Language
nameLabel: Languages in which tenders or requests to participate may be submitted
descriptionLabel: A language in which tenders, requests to participate, or expressions of interest may be submitted.

name: Tender Validity Deadline
nameLabel: Deadline until which the tender must remain valid
descriptionLabel: The period, from the tender submission deadline, for which tenders must remain valid.

name: Review Deadline Description
descriptionLabel: The description of the time limits for review procedures.

name: Procedure Type
descriptionLabel: The type of procurement procedure (e.g. according to the types given in the Public Procurement Directives mentioned in the recitals of this Act).

name: Procedure Accelerated
descriptionLabel: The time limit for receipt of requests to participate or of tenders in this procedure can be reduced due to a state of urgency.

name: Framework Duration Justification
nameLabel: Justification for the duration of the framework agreement
descriptionLabel: The justification for exceptional cases when the duration of framework agreements exceeds the legal limits.

name: Framework Buyer Categories
descriptionLabel: Any additional categories of buyers participating in the framework agreement and not mentioned by name (e.g. 'all hospitals in the Tuscany region').

name: Framework Maximum Participants Number
descriptionLabel: The maximum number of participants in the framework agreement.

name: GPA Coverage
nameLabel: The procurement is covered by the Government Procurement Agreement (GPA)
descriptionLabel: The procurement is covered by the Government Procurement Agreement (GPA).

name: GPA Coverage
nameLabel: The procurement is covered by the Government Procurement Agreement (GPA)
descriptionLabel: The procurement is covered by the Government Procurement Agreement (GPA).

name: Notice Framework Maximum Value
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreements in this procedure
descriptionLabel: The maximum value which can be spent within the framework agreement(s) announced in this notice over its/their whole duration, in all lots, including options and renewals, as calculated on the basis of the winner’s tender or winners’ tenders.

name: Dynamic Purchasing System Termination
nameLabel: The dynamic purchasing system is terminated
descriptionLabel: The dynamic purchasing system is terminated. No further contracts, besides those published in this notice, will be awarded in the dynamic purchasing system. This field can be used even if no contracts are awarded in the contract award notice.

name: No Negotiation Necessary
nameLabel: The buyer reserves the right to award the contract on the basis of the initial tenders without any further negotiations
descriptionLabel: The buyer reserves the right to award the contract on the basis of the initial tenders without any further negotiations.

name: Electronic Auction Description
descriptionLabel: Any additional information about the electronic auction.

name: Electronic Auction URL
nameLabel: An electronic auction is held at the following address
descriptionLabel: The internet address of the electronic auction.

name: Tool Atypical URL
descriptionLabel: Electronic communication requires the use of tools and devices that are not generally available. The uniform resource locator (e.g. the web address) which gives unrestricted and full direct access to these tools and devices.

name: Tool Atypical URL
descriptionLabel: Electronic communication requires the use of tools and devices that are not generally available. The uniform resource locator (e.g. the web address) which gives unrestricted and full direct access to these tools and devices.

name: Previous Planning Identifier
descriptionLabel: The identifier of a prior information notice or another similar notice related to this notice.

name: Previous Planning Identifier
descriptionLabel: The identifier of a prior information notice or another similar notice related to this notice.

name: Future Notice
nameLabel: Estimated date of publication of a contract notice within this procedure
descriptionLabel: The estimated date of publication of a contract notice within this procedure.

name: Dispatch Invitation Tender
nameLabel: Estimated date of dispatch of the invitations to submit tenders
descriptionLabel: The estimated date of dispatch of the invitations to submit tenders in two (or more) stage procedures.

name: Deadline Receipt Tenders
descriptionLabel: The time limit for receipt of tenders.

name: Deadline Receipt Tenders
descriptionLabel: The time limit for receipt of tenders.

name: Public Opening Date
descriptionLabel: The date and time for the public opening of tenders.

name: Public Opening Date
descriptionLabel: The date and time for the public opening of tenders.

name: Public Opening Place
descriptionLabel: The place (e.g. physical address, URL) where the tenders will be publicly opened.

name: Public Opening Description
descriptionLabel: Further information about the public opening of tenders. (For example, who may participate in the opening and whether any authorisation is needed.)

name: Direct Award Justification Text
descriptionLabel: The justification for using a procedure which allows directly awarding contracts, i.e. a procedure that does not require publishing a call for competition in the Official Journal of the European Union.

name: Direct Award Justification Code
descriptionLabel: A justification for using a procedure which allows directly awarding contracts, i.e. a procedure that does not require publishing a call for competition in the Official Journal of the European Union.

name: Purpose Lot Identifier
descriptionLabel: NULL

name: Purpose Lot Identifier
descriptionLabel: NULL

name: Purpose Lot Identifier
descriptionLabel: NULL

name: Change Reason Code
descriptionLabel: The main reason for the change in the notice compared to the original notice.

name: Change Description
descriptionLabel: The description of changes in the notice compared to the original notice.

name: Winner Chosen
descriptionLabel: Whether a winner was chosen.

name: Not Awarded Reason
nameLabel: The reason why a winner was not chosen
descriptionLabel: The reason for not choosing a winner.

name: Contract Conclusion Date
nameLabel: Date of the conclusion of the contract
descriptionLabel: The date when the contract was concluded. Typically, this is the date when the last contractual party signed the contract. However, if no contract is signed, then the date of contract conclusion may correspond to other dates (e.g. the date when the buyer notified the winning tenderer). The date of contract conclusion is always later than the end of the standstill period and the moment when any evidence submitted by the winner has been verified.

name: Contract Identifier
descriptionLabel: An identifier of the contract or, in case of voluntary-ex ante transparency notices and design contest result notices, of the decision. The information in the contract section refers to this contract or decision.

name: Contract URL
descriptionLabel: The uniform resource locator (e.g. the web address) of the contract.

name: Group Framework Maximum Value
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreements in this group of lots
descriptionLabel: It is the re-calculated maximum value likely to be spent for a group of lots within the procedure. This information can be provided when the maximum value of a group of lots is lower than the sum of values of individual lots (e.g. when the same budget is shared for several lots). The value covers all contracts to be awarded within a framework agreement over its whole duration, including options and renewals. The value is re-calculated on the basis of the winner’s tender or winners’ tenders.

name: Group Framework Maximum Value
nameLabel: Maximum value of the framework agreement within the group of lots
descriptionLabel: The maximum value which may be spent in a framework agreement within a group of lots. This information can be provided when the maximum value of a group of lots is lower than the sum of maximum values of individual lots in this group (e.g. when the same budget is shared for several lots). Maximum value means a value covering all contracts to be awarded within a framework agreement over its whole duration, including options and renewals.

name: Concession Revenue Buyer
nameLabel: Estimated revenue coming from the buyer who granted the concession
descriptionLabel: The estimated revenue coming from the buyer who granted the concession (e.g. prizes and payments).

name: Notice Value
nameLabel: Value of all contracts awarded in this procedure
descriptionLabel: The value of all contracts awarded in this notice, including options and renewals.

name: Concession Revenue User
nameLabel: Estimated revenue coming from the users of the concession
descriptionLabel: The estimated revenue coming from the users of the concession (e.g. fees and fines).

name: Concession Value Description
nameLabel: Method used for calculating the estimated value of the concession
descriptionLabel: The description of the method used for calculating the estimated value of the concession and any other relevant information concerning the value of the concession.

name: Winner Size
descriptionLabel: The size of the winner, tenderer or subcontractor (e.g. micro enterprise, small enterprise, medium enterprise).

name: Tender Rank
nameLabel: Rank in the list of winners
descriptionLabel: The position of the tender (i.e. whether the tender ended up first, second, third, etc.) in a design contest, a framework agreement with multiple winners (e.g. cascades), an innovation partnership, a competitive dialogue, or another procedure.

name: Country Origin
nameLabel: Country of origin of the product or the service
descriptionLabel: A country of origin of the product or the service.

name: Tender Variant
descriptionLabel: The tender is a variant.

descriptionLabel: Identifier of the field that shall not be immediately published. Only fields concerning the Result value and groups of fields concerning the Tender and Procedure Lot Result can be unpublished. In the case of the European Parliament and Council Directive 2014/25/EU, the award criteria, the procurement procedure, certain dates and in certain cases information about the nature and quantity of a service can be unpublished as well.

name: Received Submissions Type
descriptionLabel: The type of tenders or requests to participate received. The total number of tenders received shall be given. When a notice does not fall under Directive 2009/81/EC and is not about social or other specific services, the number of tenders received from micro, small and medium enterprises; the number of tenders received from tenderers registered in other European Economic Area countries and the number of tenders received from tenderers registered in countries outside of the European Economic Area shall also be given. All tenders shall be counted, regardless of whether they are admissible or inadmissible. For tenders submitted by a group of tenderers (e.g. a consortium), the tender shall be counted in the relevant category (e.g. SME) if the majority of the work is expected to be done by tenderers which fall within this category (e.g. they are SMEs).
